# Build artifacts are compared BYTE-FOR-BYTE by scripts/check-dist-drift.mjs, so git must not
# rewrite their line endings on checkout.
#
# Without this, on Windows (core.autocrlf=true, the installer default) git checks dist/ out with
# CRLF while `wxt build` writes LF. The drift check then reports "dist/ is stale" on a FRESH
# CLONE, with no source change whatsoever — and the two gates become unsatisfiable at the same
# time: check:dist passes only when the working tree holds LF, `git status` is clean only when
# it holds CRLF.
#
# That lands on the first line of ACCEPTANCE.md ("local gates pass and dist is in sync"), so the
# team test would have opened on a failure that is not a failure. Measured 2026-07-19: with the
# line endings normalised, the committed and freshly built files were byte-identical.
#
# ADR 0017 accepted a committed dist/ with a drift check as the guard. This is the guard's own
# platform assumption, made explicit.
dist/** -text

# The self-hosted ONNX Runtime pair is binary//vendored — never touch it either.
public/ort/** -text
